# Why: Documenso's email-domains UI is gated behind `IS_BILLING_ENABLED()` —
#      both the index page (`/o/<org>/settings/email-domains`) and the
#      per-domain detail page (`/o/<org>/settings/email-domains/<id>`) early-
#      return `null` (rendering a blank page) when billing is disabled. On a
#      self-host where `NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_BILLING_ENABLED` is unset/false,
#      this means the email-domains feature is unreachable via UI even though:
#        - The route exists
#        - The TRPC procedures behind it work fine
#        - Our BIZRETHINK claim (overlay 001) has `emailDomains: true`
#        - The downstream UI logic correctly handles both the
#          `isEmailDomainsEnabled` true/false cases via a separate branch
#
#      The early return is a self-host paywall artefact — Documenso's cloud
#      product treats email-domains as a paid feature, so they hide the UI
#      from non-billing customers. For self-host where the claim flag is the
#      gate, the billing check is wrong.
#
#      Fix: remove the `if (!IS_BILLING_ENABLED()) return null;` block from
#      both files. The downstream branches already handle the correct
#      behaviour:
#        - If claim has emailDomains: true → render the data table + add-domain
#          dialog
#        - If claim has emailDomains: false → render a "Currently email
#          domains can only be configured for Platform and above plans"
#          alert with a link to billing (which is harmless on self-host and
#          would never display for our BIZRETHINK orgs)
#
#      The unused `IS_BILLING_ENABLED` import is removed from both files to
#      satisfy lint.
#
# Why-not-additive: the gate lives inside the route component's render
#      function. The only way to bypass it is to edit the component. There
#      is no prop, env var, or feature flag exposed by upstream for this.
#
# Upstream-merge-fragility: LOW. Two surgical removals (one early-return
#      block + one unused import per file). Documenso doesn't change these
#      route files frequently — last-touch git log shows email-domains was
#      added in mid-2025 and the file structure has been stable since.
#
# Side note: this is the SAME paywall pattern we'll likely hit again on:
#        - branding settings UI (`o.$orgUrl.settings.branding.tsx`)
#        - org-settings layout that may suppress nav links
#      Audit those as part of cutover prep if branding-per-tenant is needed.
#      Today, only email-domains is blocking Phase A.
#
# Status: APPLIED 2026-04-30 (Phase A blocker — caught when the user opened
#         /o/mfg/settings/email-domains and saw a blank page).

diff --git a/apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/o.$orgUrl.settings.email-domains._index.tsx b/apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/o.$orgUrl.settings.email-domains._index.tsx
